/*!
\page string_strrep STRREP String Replace Function

<p>
Section: \ref sec_string "String Functions"
\section Usage
Replace every occurance of one string with another.  The
general syntax for its use is
\verbatim
  p = strrep(source,find,replace)
\endverbatim
Every instance of the string <tt>find</tt> in the string <tt>source</tt> is
replaced with the string <tt>replace</tt>.  Any of <tt>source</tt>, <tt>find</tt>
and <tt>replace</tt> can be a cell array of strings, in which case
each entry has the replace operation applied.
\section Example
Here are some examples of the use of <tt>strrep</tt>.  First the case
where are the arguments are simple strings

\if FRAGMENT
frag_string_strrep_000.m
0
strrep('Matlab is great','Matlab','FreeMat')
\endif


\verbinclude frag_string_strrep_000.m.out 

And here we have the replace operation for a number of strings:

\if FRAGMENT
frag_string_strrep_001.m
0
strrep({'time is money';'A stitch in time';'No time for games'},'time','money')
\endif


\verbinclude frag_string_strrep_001.m.out 

